==Portuguese==

===Noun 1===
- '''[[crase]]''' – s.f.   (cra.se) 
# [[Assimilation]] of [[sound]]s of two [[identical]] [[vowal]]s, [[throughout]] the [[evolution]] [[process]] of a [[language]]. [[For instance]], the [[Old]] [[Portuguese]] [[word]] “[[door]]” ([[pain]]) has [[become]], [[with time]], the word “[[dor]]” ([[pain]]).  [[Compare]] [[elisão]]: [[elision]].

===Noun 2===
- '''[[crase]]''' – s.f  (cra.se) 
# {{ptgrammar}} Name given to the processs of the  [[contraction]] of  “a + a”, [[that is]], a [[merge]] ([[assimilation]]) of the Portuguese [[preposition]] “a” [to, for] + the [[article]] “a” [the]. Both preposition and article “a” belong to the feminine gender in Portuguese. They must, accordingly, be used before feminine words. The [[translation]] of [[à]] in English, [[hence]], is [[to the]]. [[People]] [[sometimes]] [[write]] “a” [[when]] they [[should]] write “à” [[and vice versa]]. 


